Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.51,0:10:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought there might be a common thread among the memories she's forgotten,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.09,0:10:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't see any tendencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.08,0:10:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, do the relatives she has forgotten\N have anything in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.76,0:10:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they all live across the river, so we don't even see them at the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.79,0:10:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She simply forgets things that she has the least frequent contact with first?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.90,0:10:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, if that was the case, she could've forgotten her husband long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.25,0:10:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very late, but it doesn't look at all\N like she is going to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.34,0:10:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. She says she can't sleep even though she tries.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.76,0:11:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, as she works the loom all night like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.48,0:11:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,she thinks about Dad over and over \Nso that she won't forget him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.19,0:11:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So that's it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.29,0:11:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If only she could at least sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.85,0:11:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd make the waiting easier...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.79,0:11:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The warm breeze...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.40,0:11:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The fragrance of flowers...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.73,0:11:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The sound of the loom...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.06,0:11:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Normally, a night like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.54,0:11:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,2813)\i1}draws people into a deep, deep slumber...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.12,0:11:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's finally beginning to nod off...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.57,0:12:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's already awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's already morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.13,0:12:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Breakfast... breakfast...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.70,0:12:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.19,0:12:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's... just as I suspected...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.49,0:12:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A mushi that eats memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.01,0:12:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's called {\i1}kagedama.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.78,0:12:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a dark, translucent, curtain-like mushi
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.33,0:12:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that likes to submerge in the shadows of large, old trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.90,0:12:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There, it waits for people and animals to rest,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.77,0:12:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and as they begin to fall asleep, it enters their brain through their ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:13:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The host becomes unable to sleep much...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.73,0:13:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and gradually loses its memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.28,0:13:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's in the shadow of the cherry tree in our yard?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.08,0:13:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it feeds on enough memory, it divides,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.29,0:13:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and sends its clone out when its\N host is asleep for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.40,0:13:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The clone then hides in the shadows of trees. That's how they reproduce.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.95,0:13:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,By nature, they are fragile and vanish if the sun strikes them for too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.37,0:13:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But if they hide in the body, \Nthey go deep inside the brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's nothing can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.55,0:13:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean it's incurable?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.29,0:13:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunlight is the only known weakness of {\i1}kagedama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.10,0:13:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't cast a light inside the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.54,0:13:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you may be able to protect the memories you don't want to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.44,0:14:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, suppose memories are stored in a series of drawers inside your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.98,0:14:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dumplings, far away relatives and sneezes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.70,0:14:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They're categorized and stored \Nin countless different drawers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.39,0:14:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kagedama{\i0} pull them out along with the drawers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.59,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The order has nothing to do with your interest, and appears to be random.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.05,0:14:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there is one set of memories that the {\i1}kagedama{\i0} hasn't attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.94,0:14:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The things you do repeatedly every day, see every day and think every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.52,0:14:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How to cook rice, weave on the loom,\N memories of your son...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.58,0:14:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and the husband in your memory...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.21,0:14:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kagedama{\i0} may be leaving memories of the basics of daily life for last
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.74,0:15:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in order not to kill its host...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.04,0:15:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I won't forget those memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.88,0:15:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, although it's only my conjecture...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.04,0:15:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And if your memories start becoming depleted later,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.55,0:15:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it might prey on those memories, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.87,0:15:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I can suggest you do to deal with it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.78,0:15:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is to store up as many memories as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.27,0:15:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and recall the things you don't want \Nto forget over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.53,0:15:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. I'll do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.53,0:15:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Mom. You should go out rather than wait quietly at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.01,0:15:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right... maybe I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.75,0:15:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll go find your father\N instead of waiting at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.58,0:15:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.47,0:15:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop making such a silly face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been actually thinking about \Ndoing that for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.69,0:16:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was afraid of finding out \Nwhat happened to your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.10,0:16:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've had enough of waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.11,0:16:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But how do you plan to?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.05,0:16:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father often talked about a city to the west...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.05,0:16:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll start from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.21,0:16:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Will she be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.05,0:16:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll come with me, won't you, Kaji?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.78,0:16:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll let you off here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.22,0:16:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.83,0:16:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.41,0:16:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank {\i1}you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.51,0:16:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a safe trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.50,0:16:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.95,0:16:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about a year later that I learned...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.75,0:16:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,...whether or not that decision was \Nthe right  for the two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.33,0:17:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. So you're back...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.08,0:17:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Ginko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.33,0:17:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome! What would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.78,0:17:12.32,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\frz4.706\pos(338,550)}Tea  Shop
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.81,0:17:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.76,0:17:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like your mom is doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.91,0:17:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.33,0:17:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you meet your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.37,0:17:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.12,0:17:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He was in the city to the west...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.11,0:17:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,living there with another family...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.40,0:17:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know him. Try the house up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.03,0:17:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go. You like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.40,0:17:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it feel good?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.92,0:17:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom! Why didn't you say something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.09,0:17:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.22,0:18:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,On our way back, Mom kept walking,\N without saying a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.80,0:18:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,She walked without eating or sleeping until...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.78,0:18:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom? Let's rest a litt...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.03,0:18:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.01,0:18:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She must've been completely exhausted...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.57,0:18:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,After she collapsed, she slept \Nwithout waking for several days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.61,0:18:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.19,0:19:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Something just left here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.16,0:19:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.87,0:19:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you looking at me like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.05,0:19:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, I slept like a log. Time to fix breakfast...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.35,0:19:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.49,0:19:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.50,0:19:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are we in this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.27,0:20:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on our way back from vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.99,0:20:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We are?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.13,0:20:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that sound?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.10,0:20:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.14,0:20:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Have something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.79,0:20:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea. I'm starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.33,0:20:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,After that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's... let's hurry back home...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.29,0:20:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That morning, other than me, things at the house, and a few personal effects...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.05,0:20:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom had lost her memory of everything she knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.65,0:20:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,During the time she was depressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.85,0:20:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,nearly all of her memories might have been eaten away...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.79,0:21:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But she hasn't forgotten how to cook rice \Nor about me, just like always.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.09,0:21:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's because, as you suggested,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.98,0:21:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,she began going out and experiencing\N many things every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.17,0:21:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She forgets most of it the next day,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.85,0:21:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but she enjoys herself every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.24,0:21:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Does she still get hardly any sleep at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.12,0:21:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she works the loom all night, just like always.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.63,0:21:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... Sounds just like always.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.30,0:21:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.35,0:21:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like always.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.62,0:21:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.33,0:21:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.02,0:21:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinner is almost ready. Go wash your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.98,0:21:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.18,0:22:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, you set an extra setting again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.33,0:22:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right... When I only need to \Nset places for you and me...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.14,0:22:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why in the world did I feel I had to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.58,0:22:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But somehow, doing this makes me feel better...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.96,0:22:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.07,0:22:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why that is?
